The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
		 Saturday, January 31, 2004 				 Jailbreak brain held
 OUR CORRESPONDENT																								Chandigarh, Jan. 30: Chandigarh police today claimed a major breakthrough in the Burail jailbreak case after arresting Narain Singh Chaura who they claimed was the mastermind.																								Three persons involved in the killing of Punjab chief minister Beant Singh escaped with another inmate on the night of January 21 by burrowing a tunnel. Six jail officials, two Central Reserve Police Force personnel and four inmates were subsequently arrested.																								We have succeeded in arresting the prime conspirator in the jailbreak case, said inspector-general of police Rajesh Kumar.																								Police said Chaura, a former chief of the militant Akal Federation, had been a regular visitor to the three who escaped.																								He has been twice trained in Pakistan and has written books on Sikh militancy, Kumar said. 
